        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When trying to assign readonly to a view helper such as formText it is translated into a type=\"hidden\" automatically.\n\n$this->formText('city', $this->directory->city, array('readonly' => 'readonly')) \n\nbecomes: \n\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"city\" value=\"Wilmette\" \/>Wilmette<\/div> \n\nI would expect:\n\n<input type=\"text\" name=\"city\" id=\"city\" value=\"Wilmette\" readonly=\"readonly\" \/>\n\nI believe the code in FormElement.php is responsible for the behavior :   \n{code}\n        \/\/ disable if readonly \n        if (isset($info['attribs']['readonly']) && \n            $info['attribs']['readonly'] == 'readonly') { \n            \/\/ disable the element \n            $info['disable'] = true; \n            unset($info['attribs']['readonly']); \n        } \n        \n        \/\/ normal disable, overrides readonly \n        if (isset($info['attribs']['disable']) && \n            $info['attribs']['disable']) { \n            \/\/ disable the element \n            $info['disable'] = true; \n            unset($info['attribs']['disable']); \n        } \n{code}\n"
        },
