        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13765",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jscherer26",
                        "name": "jscherer26",
                        "displayName": "James Scherer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Looking further into this it appears that this was done intentionally. I can't find a Zend_View or Zend_View_Helper proposal, so I'm not sure why the disable code exists. My guess would be that initially this fuctionallity was intended to be able disable a form as a whole, and then wasn't implimented fully or correctly. Each of the individual form helpers is coded to check $disable and take action. \n\n{code}\n    public function formText($name, $value = null, $attribs = null)\n    {\n        $info = $this->_getInfo($name, $value, $attribs);\n        extract($info); \/\/ name, value, attribs, options, listsep, disable\n        \n        \/\/ build the element\n        if ($disable) {\n            \/\/ disabled\n            $xhtml = $this->_hidden($name, $value)\n                   . htmlspecialchars($value, ENT_COMPAT, 'UTF-8');\n        } else {\n            \/\/ enabled\n            $xhtml = '<input type=\"text\"'\n                   . ' name=\"' . htmlspecialchars($name, ENT_COMPAT, 'UTF-8') . '\"'\n                   . ' id=\"' . htmlspecialchars($id, ENT_COMPAT, 'UTF-8') . '\"'\n                   . ' value=\"' . htmlspecialchars($value, ENT_COMPAT, 'UTF-8') . '\"'\n                   . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\n                   . ' \/>';\n        }\n        \n        return $xhtml;\n    }\n{code}\n\nMaybe the feeling was that this was a more universally excepted by browsers, I clearly don't know. But it is preventing me from getting the desired behavior and appears to be a bug.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jscherer26",
                        "name": "jscherer26",
                        "displayName": "James Scherer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-28T12:01:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-28T12:01:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13895",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Behaviour fixed in r4320. 'readonly' attrib now correctly set to 'readonly', and the element is no longer disabled.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-03T06:48:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-03T06:48:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13912",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jscherer26",
                        "name": "jscherer26",
                        "displayName": "James Scherer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is minor. There is a comment in the code in FormElement.php  that no longer applies.\n\n* Note that you cannot pass a 'disable' param'; you need to pass\n* it as an 'attribs' key. A \"'readonly' => 'readonly'\" attribs\n* key-value pair has the same effect as \"'disable' => true\".\n\n\n\n\n",
